Shampoo always meant tantrum until we discovered Spoo from @curatiobaby 
 
Spoo is a mild, tear-free, and sulphate-free shampoo specially formulated for baby’s fine and delicate hair. The mild ingredients moisturize and cleanse the hair and scalp, making it soft and shiny.
 
You should definitely use it for Cradle cap which can be resolved easily by following 2 simple steps.

1. Use a mild baby shampoo like Spoo to loosen the scales like spoo @curatiobaby 

2. Brush away the scales from the scalp by using a soft baby brush
Spoo helps in preventing and treating this condition too.
 
Once you start using it you will never stop using it. We love it and absolutely recommend spoo. 

@curatiobaby

They say diamonds are a girl’s best friend, but even so, it’s so important to choose the right ones! @limelightdiamonds is my go-to when it comes to picking up real diamonds that are sustainable and eco friendly. ✨ 

What’s different about these diamonds? 
They’re not mined but instead grown above in labs in exactly the same way! So they end up saving huge tonnes of land and gallons of water that is destroyed in mining - something that is so critical in current times where our environment & planet needs our attention and care. These are 100% real and pure diamonds yet very affordable.
You can check out their versatile collection that’s beautiful and intricately made that you can carry for timeless occasions making it a worthwhile investment. 

Store : 301, Relcon House, Trimbak Niwas, MG Road, Vile Parle (East), Mumbai 400057

Link : http://www.limelightdiamonds.com/

#Repost @dolly.jain with @use.repost
・・・
Here’s another adorable hand-painted organza saree! 🥰 The detailing is just stunning—every little motif is hand-painted with so much love, you can actually feel the emotions in every line, every thought, and every brushstroke. That’s the magic of something made by hand instead of a machine—it just feels extra special and precious.

Today, I want to dedicate this post to my dear friend Parul Garg who just became a grandmother to a baby boy! I’m so, so happy for her. The moment I heard the news, I was over the moon—especially because her daughter was once my bride. I can only imagine how excited Parul must be right now!

It’s amazing,  how some people start as clients and end up becoming your closest friends. Life is truly beautiful that way.

And a huge shoutout to @handpaintedoutfitsbyneha who painted this stunning saree in just two days! She worked so hard, day and night, to finish it on time. Even though I couldn’t make it to the event, I just had to share this reel with you all so you know how much this saree means to me—so much love and emotion in one piece!

Saree @handpaintedoutfitsbyneha 
D’Coat @iambydollyjain
